The paper focuses on intrinsic methods to detect overfitting in machine learning models, which suggests that it is likely to belong to the Machine Learning (cs.LG) or Artificial Intelligence (cs.AI) sub-categories. The use of logic circuits and analysis of the flow of training examples through the model suggests that it may also belong to the Neural and Evolutionary Computing (cs.NE) sub-category. The mention of limitations and future work related to robustness and adversarial settings suggests that it may also belong to the Cryptography and Security (cs.CR) or Systems and Control (cs.SY) sub-categories.
